1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,400
A couple of days ago I saw a friend buy a Rimowa suitcase, so I jumped on the trend and spent over two thousand dollars on it. I regretted it.

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:15,700
Because this new suitcase is just such a great deal - less than a tenth of Rimowa's price - and in everyday use it does three things noticeably better.

3
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:41,400
I bought Rimowa in the first place for its smooth wheels and high-end look. But I tested it myself: even a premium Rimowa wheel spins five seconds at most, while this one keeps going for over a hundred seconds, about twenty times smoother. Rolling through an airport or station, you barely hear a sound. Each wheel has its own built-in spring, so even on gravel it cushions the vibration.

4
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:57,300
The second thing is capacity. Rimowa uses the Equal Split Design - equal space on both sides - so anything bulky just won't let it close. This one's 30/70 deep-cabin design swallows larger items easily, and the extra room still fits a backpack.

5
00:00:57,300 --> 00:01:11,600
The third is the handle and wheels. With Rimowa, switching to a new color scheme easily runs into the hundreds, even over a thousand. Here, the handle and wheels detach freely and come in seven matching colors you can mix whatever you like - a new set of parts is basically a brand-new case.

6
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:25,500
Same aluminum-magnesium alloy, lower price, smoother wheels, more room inside. Best of all, buy now and - on top of the set it already includes - the spare wheel-set box that normally sells for 60 dollars comes free when you order through the shop today. Come take a look.
